text: Gusinoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Ozernovsky Selsoviet of Ikryaninsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 46 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 76 km from Astrakhan, 30 km from Ikryanoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ikryaninsky District
title: Gusinoye
